MonitoringLocationName: Snake River at Old Flagg Ranch 1000' Below Bridge
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: North bank of Snake River 180 feet west of power pole.  Located on right bank about 1000 feet downstream of Rte. 89 bridge.  The sampling location is located in the floodplain and is void of brushy or woody vegetation.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Snake River Below Site of New Visitor's Center
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Site is located about 500 feet downstream of Moose Bridge/USGS Gage Station.  The site has a homogenous flow just before a gravel island that splits the flow about 600 feet below the site.  The site is on right bank floodplain and on the left bank a secondary high flow channel located runs parallel with the Snake River..

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Firehole River - 100 meters downstream from USGS Gage
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is located near the mouth of the Firehole River on the west side of Yellowstone National Park.  The river basin of the Firehole River encompasses approximately 73,038 hectares and drains much of the west-central portion of Yellowstone.  The Firehole River is heavily influenced by the many thermal features that drain into the river and runs parallel to a portion of the south-loop road.  A USGS gage station is located approximately 100 meters upstream of the sample site.
HorizontalCollectionMethodName: GPS Code (Pseudo Range) Standard Position (SA Off)
VerticalCollectionMethodName: GPS Code (Pseudo Range) Standard Position (SA Off)

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Gibbon River at Bridge .5m south of Madison Junction
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: The watershed of the Gibbon River drains much of the west-central portions of Yellowstone National Park.  There are hundreds of thermal features that drain into the Gibbon River which include the Norris Geyser basin.  The plethora of thermal features found along the length of the Gibbon River have an effect on temperature regimes, dissolved solutes and acidity which ultimately affect the overall water quality.  The sample location is approximately 1/2 mile from the confluence of the Firehole and Madison Rivers.
HorizontalCollectionMethodName: GPS Code (Pseudo Range) Standard Position (SA Off)
VerticalCollectionMethodName: GPS Code (Pseudo Range) Standard Position (SA Off)

The sample location is approximately 1/2 mile from the Yellowstone River near Lamar Ranger station and is located at the USGS gaging station on the Lamar River.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Soda Butte Creek (lower)
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This water quality site is located near the confluence of Soda Butte Creek with Lamar River in the northeast portion of Yellowstone National Park and is near a USGS gaging station.  The watershed upstream of the sample site encompasses approximately 25,640 hectares.  The Soda Butte watershed drains a large portions of the northeast corner of Yellowstone National Park.  Stream water quality has the potential to be affected by the McClaren mine tailings in which the stream flows through near Cooke City, MT which is near the headwaters of Soda Butte Creek.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Soda Butte Creek (upper)
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This water quality site is located near the northeast entrance of Yellowstone National Park at the park boundary near Silver Gate, MT.  The watershed upstream of the sample site encompasses approximately 8,081 hectares.  Most of the water draining this area originates outside of park boundaries and flows into the park at the sample site.  Stream water quality can be affected by the McClaren mine tailings in which the stream flows through near Cooke City, MT.  This is a real time USGS gaging station.  Drainage area is 31.2 square miles.  Record for this site maintained by the USGS Montana Water Science Center.
